{"id": 14358, "date": "1987-04-02T11:00:00", "date_gmt": "1987-04-02T19:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=14358"}, "modified": "2026-06-10T14:42:36", "modified_gmt": "2026-06-10T21:42:36", "slug": "matr-bruce-springsteen-and-jah-love-one-love-people-get-ready", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/1987/04/02/matr-bruce-springsteen-and-jah-love-one-love-people-get-ready/", "title": {"rendered": "One Love"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>Bob Marley&#8217;s signature song &#8220;One Love&#8221; might seem like a strange candidate for a Bruce Springsteen cover, but when Bruce and Clarence joined Jah Love, a local New Jersey-based reggae singer, on stage at a Jersey shore club in the summer of 1987, that&#8217;s exactly what they performed together.</p>\n<p>(At least, until they segued from &#8220;One Love&#8221; into one of Bruce&#8217;s own songs. I&#8217;ll let you figure out which one for yourself&#8211;suffice it to say it&#8217;s just about the last arrangement you&#8217;d ever expect to hear for it.)</p>\n<div id=\"v-EYKIYAgU-1\" class=\"video-player\"><iframe title='VideoPress Video Player' aria-label='VideoPress Video Player' width='758' height='426' src='https://videopress.com/embed/EYKIYAgU?hd=1&amp;cover=1&amp;loop=0&amp;autoPlay=0&amp;permalink=1&amp;muted=0&amp;controls=1&amp;playsinline=0&amp;useAverageColor=0&amp;preloadContent=metadata' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen data-resize-to-parent=\"true\" allow='clipboard-write'></iframe><script data-jetpack-boost=\"ignore\" src='https://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/video/assets/js/next/videopress-iframe.js'></script></div>\n<p>As for their &#8220;One Love&#8221; cover&#8230; well, let&#8217;s just say it&#8217;s not one of Bruce&#8217;s best attempts.</p>\n<p>Then again, it&#8217;s hard to top Marley&#8217;s original&#8211;it remains one of the most universally recognized and loved reggae songs.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/IN0KkGeEURw?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>One Love/People Get Ready<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> July 30, 1987 (Neptune, NJ)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> July 30, 1987 (Neptune, NJ)</p>\n<p>\u00a9 November 28, 2019</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>One time only: Bruce joins New Jersey reggae singer Jah Love for a game cover of Bob Marley&#8217;s beloved classic, &#8220;One Love,&#8221; in the summer of 1987.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 69850, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_feature_clip_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false}, "categories": [4, 3617, 5], "tags": [2556, 1364, 2555], "class_list": ["post-14358", "post", "type-post", "status-publish", "format-standard", "has-post-thumbnail", "hentry", "category-cover-me", "category-it-takes-two", "category-meeting-across-the-river", "tag-bob-marley-the-wailers", "tag-jah-love", "tag-one-love-people-get-ready"], "aioseo_notices": [], "jetpack_publicize_connections": [], "jetpack_featured_media_url": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/admin-ajax-2026-06-10T144105.155.jpg?fit=1200%2C1200&ssl=1", "jetpack_sharing_enabled": true, "jetpack_shortlink": "https://wp.me/p9w3Lk-3JA", "jetpack_likes_enabled": true, "jetpack-related-posts": [{"id": 57850, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2025/07/30/kingdom-of-days-july-30-2/", "url_meta": {"origin": 14358, "position": 0}, "title": "July 30", "author": "Ken", "date": "July 30, 2025", "format": false, "excerpt": "On this date: Bruce releases The Rising, his first E Street Band album in 18 years. Watch the day's festivities inside. Plus: the premiere of \"All the Way Home\" in 1992, reggae versions of \"Born in the U.S.A.\" and \"My Hometown,\" and more.", "rel": "", "context": "In &quot;Kingdom of Days&quot;", "block_context": {"text": "Kingdom of Days", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/category/kingdom-of-days/"}, "img": {"alt_text": "", "src": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/rising.jpg?fit=1200%2C1200&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200", "width": 350, "height": 200, "srcset": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/rising.jpg?fit=1200%2C1200&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200 1x, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/rising.jpg?fit=1200%2C1200&ssl=1&resize=525%2C300 1.5x, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/rising.jpg?fit=1200%2C1200&ssl=1&resize=700%2C400 2x, https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/rising.jpg?fit=1200%2C1200&ssl=1&resize=1050%2C600 3x"}, "classes": []}, {"id": 59422, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2025/08/26/kingdom-of-days-august-26-2/", "url_met